<%- include('partials/header', { 
  title: 'The Western Provinces',
  extraCss: 'world.css',
  extraHead: `
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/leaflet/1.9.4/leaflet.min.css" />
    <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/leaflet/1.9.4/leaflet.min.js"></script>
  `
}) %>

<section>
  <h1>The Western Provinces</h1>
  <p>
    The Western Provinces is, fractured region on the edge of the
    former Allyrian Empire. For centuries, the land was connected by well maintained roads,
    cities, and shared rule, but that ended after two long winters devastated
    the population and forced the empire to withdraw.
  </p>
  <p>
    Today, the Provinces are a patchwork of hundreds of independent city-states. Large cities, 
    fortified towns, and smaller strongholds trade, fight, and form shifting alliances. 
    Outside the settlements, much of the land has fallen into ruin or wilderness. Travel between 
    them is always uncertain and dangerous.
  </p>
  <p>
    The interactive hex map below requires zooming in to interact with individual hexes. 
    Currently, only hex (69,32) contains detailed information. Other hexes display placeholder text and will 
    be filled in as development continues.
  </p>
</section>

<section id="map-box">
  <button id="fs-btn" title="Fullscreen">⛶</button>
  <div id="map"></div>
</section>

<aside id="info-overlay">
  <article id="info">
    <button id="info-close">✕</button>
    <h3 id="info-name">—</h3>
    <p id="info-desc"></p>
    <section id="info-body"></section>
    <footer id="info-coords"></footer>
  </article>
</aside>

<section id="controls">
  <label>
    <input type="checkbox" id="hex-toggle" checked /> Show hex grid
  </label>
  <label>
    <input type="checkbox" id="labels-toggle" checked /> Show labels
  </label>
  <output id="coords">lat: — lng: —</output>
</section>

<script src="/js/world.js"></script>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>